name: matrix_ops
jaxpr:
{ lambda ; a:f32[2,2] b:f32[2,2]. let
    c:f32[2,2] = transpose[permutation=(1, 0)] b
    d:f32[2,2] = dot_general[
      dimension_numbers=(([1], [0]), ([], []))
      preferred_element_type=float32
    ] a c
    e:i32[2,2] = iota[dimension=0 dtype=int32 shape=(2, 2) sharding=None] 
    f:i32[2,2] = iota[dimension=1 dtype=int32 shape=(2, 2) sharding=None] 
    g:i32[2,2] = add e 0:i32[]
    h:bool[2,2] = eq g f
    i:f32[2,2] = convert_element_type[new_dtype=float32 weak_type=False] h
    j:f32[2,2] = add d i
  in (j,) }
hlo:
module @jit_matrix_ops attributes {mhlo.num_partitions = 1 : i32, mhlo.num_replicas = 1 : i32} {
  func.func public @main(%arg0: tensor<2x2xf32>, %arg1: tensor<2x2xf32>) -> (tensor<2x2xf32> {jax.result_info = "result"}) {
    %0 = stablehlo.transpose %arg1, dims = [1, 0] : (tensor<2x2xf32>) -> tensor<2x2xf32>
    %1 = stablehlo.dot_general %arg0, %0, contracting_dims = [1] x [0], precision = [DEFAULT, DEFAULT] : (tensor<2x2xf32>, tensor<2x2xf32>) -> tensor<2x2xf32>
    %2 = stablehlo.iota dim = 0 : tensor<2x2xi32>
    %3 = stablehlo.iota dim = 1 : tensor<2x2xi32>
    %c = stablehlo.constant dense<0> : tensor<i32>
    %4 = stablehlo.broadcast_in_dim %c, dims = [] : (tensor<i32>) -> tensor<2x2xi32>
    %5 = stablehlo.add %2, %4 : tensor<2x2xi32>
    %6 = stablehlo.compare  EQ, %5, %3,  SIGNED : (tensor<2x2xi32>, tensor<2x2xi32>) -> tensor<2x2xi1>
    %7 = stablehlo.convert %6 : (tensor<2x2xi1>) -> tensor<2x2xf32>
    %8 = stablehlo.add %1, %7 : tensor<2x2xf32>
    return %8 : tensor<2x2xf32>
  }
}
